The paper discusses a method for parameter estimation in graphical models using SAME, which is a popular approach in machine learning and falls under the category of probabilistic graphical models. The paper also mentions the use of modern hardware and parallelism, which suggests a focus on optimization and performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions Latent Dirichlet Allocation, which is a popular topic in natural language processing, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
